issue_body:
(This is copied from #220 for follow up)

Initial Issue: Somehow the Devices has only RTL-TCP enabled, and all other devices options are greyed out. I enabled it uder ~/.config/urh.ini, but starting reset everything back to disabled. I'm sure that my RTL-SDR is correctly installed, as gqrx is running fine. But do I need gnuradion to be able to use it under URH, as I was unable to install the full gnuradio yet?

@jopohl : For devices you should ensure that you have the required libs installed on your system. What does locate rtlsdr.so say? You should not enable devices manually in ini. Native backend should work for you if you installed rtlsdr.so, you can use the rebuild button in device options for this.

my code 

#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Created on 2017-03-10 13:58:05
# Project: tutorial_douban_movie

from pyspider.libs.base_handler import *


class Handler(BaseHandler):
    crawl_config = {
    }

    @every(minutes=24 * 60)
    def on_start(self):
        self.crawl('http://movie.douban.com/tag/',callback=self.index_page)

    @config(age=10 * 24 * 60 * 60)
    def index_page(self, response):
        for each in response.doc('a[href^="http"]').items():
            self.crawl(each.attr.href, callback=self.detail_page)

    @config(priority=2)
    def detail_page(self, response):
        return {
            "url": response.url,
            "title": response.doc('title').text(),
        }

Hi,

I am trying to the dnn_mmod_face_detection_ex example from the example set. In the example after loading the model and test image, the example executes 
     auto dets = net(img);
This function then never returns and the gets stuck inside function

const tensor& forward(const tensor& x)
        {
            subnetwork->forward(x);
            const dimpl::subnet_wrapper<subnet_type> wsub(*subnetwork);
            if (!this_layer_setup_called)
            {
                details.setup(wsub);
                this_layer_setup_called = true;
            }
            if (this_layer_operates_inplace())
                impl::call_layer_forward(details, wsub, private_get_output());
            else
                impl::call_layer_forward(details, wsub, cached_output);

            gradient_input_is_stale = true;
            return private_get_output();
        }
in core.h

 The subnetwork->forward(x); invocation seems to be the source of the problem.

