angular.module("ngViewExample").controller('UploadCtrl', ['$scope', '$http', '$timeout', '$compile', '$upload', function($scope, $http, $timeout, $compile, $upload) {

  $scope.fileReaderSupported = window.FileReader != null && (window.FileAPI == null || FileAPI.html5 != false);

  /**
   * Create a thumbnail of the selected file.
   */
  $scope.generateThumb = function(file) {
    if (file != null) {
      if ($scope.fileReaderSupported && file.type.indexOf('image') > -1) {
        $timeout(function() {
          var fileReader = new FileReader();
          fileReader.readAsDataURL(file);
          fileReader.onload = function(e) {
            $timeout(function() {
              file.dataUrl = e.target.result;
            });
          }
        });
      }
    }
  }

  /**
   * Upload the file.
   */
  $scope.myUpload = function(file){
    $scope.upload = $upload.upload({
        url: 'myuploadscript.php', 
        method: 'POST',
        file: file,
        data: {message: "Hello, this is some test data!"}
    }).success(function(data, status, headers, config) {
        // file is uploaded successfully
        if (config.file) {
          alert('file ' + config.file.name + 'is uploaded successfully. Response: ' + JSON.stringify(data));
        } else { // File uploading is NOT mandatory in my case
          alert('No file is uploaded. Response: ' + JSON.stringify(data));
        }
    });
  };

}]);
```

Providing custom deferred types results in an error
```console
TypeError: __call__() takes exactly 3 arguments (1 given)
```

The column 
```
class MyModel(DbBase):
    name = sa.Column(sa.Float(), info={'colanderalchemy': {'typ': deferred_type}})
```
The deferred type 
```
@colander.deferred
def deferred_type(node, kw):
    if kw['use_float'] == True:
          return colander.Float()
    else:
          return colander.Integer()
```

When generating the schema with SQLAlchemySchemaNode, we get the error.

The error comes from the fact that a colander.deferred has a '__call__' method.

https://github.com/stefanofontanelli/ColanderAlchemy/blob/master/colanderalchemy/schema.py#L286
An exception should be added for colander.deferreds.

If I import like this:

``` scss
@import '../../../public/vendor/bower/roboto-fontface/css/roboto-fontface';
```

Then my preprocessor complains about not knowing whether to load `.css` or `.scss`.

If I change it to this:

``` scss
@import '../../../public/vendor/bower/roboto-fontface/css/roboto-fontface.scss';
```

Then my SCSS linter complains.

Please, move the files to separate folders, like everybody else does (e.g. [FontAwesome](https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome)).

Hi,
    Recently, I add a new 'lookup parameter' in linear-encoder.cc & nerual-lm.cc ( lamtram ) . the original 'layer_size'  & 'wordrep' is set to be "512", so I set my 'layer_size2' & 'wordrep2' to be "3".

I mainly edit these .cc  & .h files
in  macros.cc:
//add by me
int lamtram::GlobalVars::layer_size2 = 3;

in linear-encoder.cc:
 // Word representations
  p_wr_W_ = model.add_lookup_parameters(vocab_size, {(unsigned int)wordrep_size});
//add by me
  p_wr_W2_ = model.add_lookup_parameters(vocab_size, {(unsigned int)wordrep_size2_});

in neural-lm.cc:
  //add by me
  if(wordrep_size2_ <= 0) wordrep_size2_ = GlobalVars::layer_size2;
  p_wr_W2_ = model.add_lookup_parameters(vocab->size(), {(unsigned int)wordrep_size2_});

My training progress is right . 
When I do decoding, the error comes out when it gets to '''lamtram.cc: loader.populate(*mod_temp);'''

The error is:
what():  Dimensions of lookup parameter /_1 lookup up from file ({3,28}) do not match parameters to be populated ({512,28})

I checked my code many times, and  tried it on Dynet2.0 & Dynet2,0.2. I really don't know why it went wrong.
Please help me~
Thanks

